# 4. How Loops Affect Space Complexity

Important:

### Loops Usually Affect Time, Not Space

Example

```java
for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    System.out.println(i);
}
```

Space Complexity:

O(1)

Reason:

Only variable i exists.

---

Nested Loops

```java
for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    for(int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
        System.out.println(i + " " + j);
    }
}
```

Time = O(n²)

Space = O(1)

---

# Interview Shortcut

Loops increase Time Complexity.

Extra arrays increase Space Complexity.

---

# 5. How Recursion Affects Space Complexity

Every recursive call creates a new stack frame.

Each frame stores:

- Parameters
- Local variables
- Return address

---

Example

```java
void fun(int n) {
    if(n == 0)
        return;

    fun(n - 1);
}
```

Call Stack:

fun(5)
↓
fun(4)
↓
fun(3)
↓
fun(2)
↓
fun(1)
↓
fun(0)

Depth = n

Space Complexity = O(n)

---

# Recursion Stack Diagram

For n = 4

Top of Stack

fun(0)
fun(1)
fun(2)
fun(3)
fun(4)

Bottom of Stack

Total Frames = 5

Space = O(n)

