# 10. Common Interview Questions

## Why Binary Search Uses O(1) Space?

Iterative Binary Search uses only:

- low
- high
- mid

No extra storage.

Space = O(1)

---

## Why Merge Sort Uses O(n) Extra Space?

Temporary arrays are created during merge.

Extra memory = n

Space = O(n)

---

## Why Recursion Causes StackOverflowError?

Too many recursive calls fill the call stack.

Example:

```java
fun(1000000);
```

Stack becomes full.

---

## Iterative vs Recursive Space

| Approach | Space |
|-----------|--------|
| Iterative | O(1) |
| Recursive | Depends on recursion depth |

---

# 11. Common Mistakes

❌ Counting loop iterations as space.

❌ Ignoring recursion stack.

❌ Ignoring temporary arrays.

❌ Confusing Time Complexity with Space Complexity.

❌ Counting input space as auxiliary space.

❌ Forgetting queue/stack memory in BFS/DFS.

